About this item

  • USB 3.0 & USB C SD Card Reader: This 2-in-1 micro SD memory card reader features USB 3.0 and USB Type C port, easily backup data or transfer file to your PC, Laptop, USB-C enabled mobile phone or tablet. Compatible with SDXC, SDHC, SD, MMC, RS-MMC, Micro SDXC, Micro SD, and Micro SDHC cards.
  • SD and TF Card Supported: Simultaneously reading and writing on 2 external memory cards (SD/Micro SD) to save the constant plugging and pulling of plugs. A convenient method to transfer files/photos/videos between the digital camera SD cards and phones or between dual memory cards, no need to occupy space on devices.
  • SuperSpeed Secure Transmission: With the powerful GL3224 chip, UGREEN SD card reader is easy to read your DSLR Camera SD memory card at 5Gbps and allows HD movies in 1GB to transfer in 10s. Support memory card capacity up to 2TB maximum, travel photos can be shared with friends anytime, anywhere. Built-in fuse to prevent short circuit and overcurrent, the USB C card reader secures high safety for all connected devices and memory cards.
  • Designed for Compact: This Micro SD card adapter is designed in a tiny size, allows to slip in and stay safe in your camera bag or backpack because of the covers for protecting the plugs. Hidden press design on the Micro SD (TF) card slot makes your TF card unnoticeable when plugged into the USB card reader, well protect your TF Card.
  • Plug and Play: No driver installation required for Windows 10/8.1/8/7/XP/Vista, macOS, iPad, Android, Chrome, Linux, just simple plug and facilitate transferring files, no additional power supply required. Whether you're on the move or just at home, this reliable SD card reader can make data transfer a lot easier.

UGREEN USB-A & USB-C 2-in-1 Memory Card Reader

  • This external card reader is the combination of USB 3.0 and USB Type C Plug, compatible with most of the USB-A device and USB-C Devices, such as PS4 / PS3, Xbox One, PC, Laptops, USB-C enabled smartphones and tablets, required no driver installation for Windows 10 / 8.1 / 8 / 7 / XP / Vista, macOS, Chrome, Linux, Android, iPadOS.
  • Features with SD and TF(Micro SD) dual card slots, support 2 cards reading and writing simultaneously. It is compatible with the memory cards on your Camcorder, DashCam, Sports Camera, DSLR Camera, Monitor, Drone, Digital Camera, can access to lightroom or playback video directly on your phone/tablets.
  • Offering 5Gbps transmission speed, a lot quicker than using Wi-Fi to backup or offload file/photos from your SD/TF Card, transfer video and photos in just seconds.

Excellent for on-the-go photography

  • This small SD card reader is easy to transfer/copy/playback your travel photos to your USB-C OTG enabled phone or tablet, sharing your photos on Facebook or other social media immediately.
  • Besides, this memory card adapter allows exchanging photos between SD and TF card, no need to download to your phone then transfer them to another card, saving time and saving battery for data transmission.

Compatible Digital Cards up to 2TB

  • SD slot: UHS-I SDXC / SDHC / SD / MMC / RS-MMC / MMC micro, such as SanDisk Ultra Class 10 UHS-I SDHC, Extreme Pro UHS-I SDXC, Kingston Canvas Select Class 10 SDHC;
  • Micro SD/TF slot: UHS-I Micro SD / Micro SDXC / Micro SDHC, such as EVO Plus Class 10 Micro SDXC, Ultra 128GB microSDXC.

Kindly Reminder

  • For Samsung S9/S9 Plus/S8/S8 Plus/Note 8/Google Pixel 2/XL/LG G5/V20/V30/ Nexus 5X6P, the memory card file format should be FAT32/EXFAT, NTFS is not supported.
  • Please kindly make sure that your USB C phone/tablet supports OTG function before purchasing.
  • Only compatible with devices of Type C / Type-A / Thunderbolt 3 interface, NOT work with Lightning / Micro USB interface like iPhone XS / XS Max / X / iPad.

      Ben Rowe
      4.0 out of 5 stars Solid performance, but expected better build and features from UGreen
      Reviewed in the United Kingdom on October 2, 2020
      Verified Purchase
      I've had a cable and charger from Ugreen and they were both as expected, but they both had a solid build.

      This adapter doesn't seem as solid as the other products I've had from this brand. Being lightweight may be a good thing, but with items this size, it doesn't really matter. The plastic used feels a bit cheap and is the easiest plastic I've come across to scratch. If it slides on your desk, you will get a permanent mark on it. Not a reason to rate it down a star, but it doesn't have a premium feel that the price suggests. The caps for both the USB C and A connector don't have a solid click and slip off easily. Comparing it to a cheaper Transcend card reader, I would say the only advantage to this is being USB 3.1 vs 3.0 and having the addition of type C.

      The main reason for rating it down a star is no LED. While I don't like how intense many brands make the glaring lights on memory devices, it is not good that this has no light. It is really helpful to have one as it helps indicate your PC is still writing/reading to the card while you do not have the file operations window open on your screen. With my transcend reader, I would be doing other things on my PC and just rely on when the LED stopped flashing to know when it was done. While your PC will tell you and there is an easy solution, it is certainly a bonus to have this feature and i think the lack of it is enough to deduct a star.

      The transfer speeds are as you would expect and while the plastic is very scratch prone as I said, it doesn't flex and seems pretty durable. The most handy thing about is is being able to plug it into my tablet's type C port to view pictures from my camera's SD card. Though android is sometimes fussy about the format of the card so is sometimes easier to do this another way.
